<node id="Deviations From The Grading Policy">
  <data key="d0">Deviations From The Grading Policy</data>
  <data key="d1">academicpolicy</data>
  <data key="d2">This policy states that requests for grade increases inconsistent with the stated grading scale will be denied to ensure fairness and consistency, as grades are based on quantifiable, objectively evaluated submissions and exams.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d55a5c42258b138ee2fec076c197b5fc</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1774753300</data>
  <data key="d6" />
</node>
<node id="Grading Policy">
  <data key="d0">Grading Policy</data>
  <data key="d1">academicpolicy</data>
  <data key="d2">The overarching policy that defines how grades for individual assignments and the course are assigned based on concrete, quantifiable, and objectively evaluated submissions and exams.&lt;SEP&gt;The policy outlining how the course grade is determined, based on various components.&lt;SEP&gt;This policy outlines the distribution of grades across various components: Assignments (31%), Quizzes (40%), Course Project (26%), and Participation (3%).</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d55a5c42258b138ee2fec076c197b5fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d09a6b6553f5acaa3272cc866340a578&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9f53b4eba20509613f45ac239b9fa370</data>
