<node id="Grading Scale">
  <data key="d0">Grading Scale</data>
  <data key="d1">academicpolicy</data>
  <data key="d2">The defined scale or standard used for assigning grades in the course, against which requests for grade increases are evaluated for consistency.&lt;SEP&gt;This policy defines the letter grades corresponding to percentage ranges: A (90-100), B (80-89), C (70-79), D (60-69), and F (&lt;60).</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d55a5c42258b138ee2fec076c197b5fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9f53b4eba20509613f45ac239b9fa370</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1774753386</data>
  <data key="d6" />
</node>
<node id="Course Specific Late Work Policy">
  <data key="d0">Course Specific Late Work Policy</data>
  <data key="d1">academicpolicy</data>
  <data key="d2">This policy outlines specific guidelines for late submissions within the course, stating that makeup work for excused absences is exempt.&lt;SEP&gt;This policy details specific late penalties for Assignments 1-3, Project Proposal, and Project Report (10-50% for 1-4 days late, 100% for 5+ days late), and prohibits late submissions for Assignment 0 and Project Presentation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-aa73fee78ff788a909465d0d4489187a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9f53b4eba20509613f45ac239b9fa370</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1774753386</data>
  <data key="d6" />
